about.summary: Provides the tables from the 'Sean Lahman Baseball Database' as a set of R data.frames. It uses the data on pitching, hitting and fielding performance and other tables from 1871 through 2018, as recorded in the 2019 version of the database. Documentation examples show how many baseball questions can be investigated.

Provides the tables from the 'Sean Lahman Baseball Database' as a set of R data.frames. name: r-lahman
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "9.0-0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-lahman
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Lahman_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/Lahman/Lahman_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: d9fa5df6a5240667555b4a15d60193f60e9f50b3904568e20975b64eb187dc60

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('Lahman')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('Lahman')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://lahman.r-forge.r-project.org/
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: Provides the tables from the 'Sean Lahman Baseball Database' as a set of R data.frames. It uses the data on pitching, hitting and fielding performance and other tables from 1871 through 2018, as recorded in the 2019 version of the database. Documentation examples show how many baseball questions can be investigated.
  license_family: GPL
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
